This bread is lovely despite the half-awake mess I made of it this morning in my rush to have something to serve for breakfast. What happened? I was doubling the recipe. I realized I'd put too little sugar into the batter--thank god I caught my mistake before it was too late. Fixed that. The batter seemed too runny so I added another bit of flour. Tasted it and couldnt understand why the spices werent coming through so I added another dose of spices. Something still seemed off but I couldnt put my finger on it. So I poured the batter into the pans anyway, popped them into the oven, closed the door, stood up, and there on the counter was the entire bowl of ALL THE DRY INGREDIENTS I'D NEGLECTED TO ADD. So I pulled the pans out of the oven, dumped their contents into the dry ingredients and mixed them together. Mixed in an extra egg as compensation for that extra flour I'd added. Cleaned the pans. Resprayed them. Poured the batter back in. Popped them back into the oven. Came out great! Yum. I've made this before, and I've made Flay's Pumpkin Bread Pudding too. (I'm allergic to corn so I can't eat Indian Pudding anymore, but his PBPud compensates for it nicely!) No rating... just wanted to share that I made a mess of it yet it still tasted great!

