WHOA. This recipe is spectacular! I love pumpkin, and this recipe exceeds all others I've tried. I will definitely make this all through the holidays this year. The other comments were super helpful, so I'll add my modifications to the fray. Like everyone else, I doubled the recipe. But I used half whole wheat and half spelt flour, used heaping portions of spices, omitted the cloves (because I'm not a fan) and substituted ground ginger. I added the zest of one orange and instead of water, I used Knudsen's Morning Blend (an orange-pineapple style juice) because I had some, except I only used 1 cup instead of 1 1/3 cup. Most importantly, I made my own roasted pumpkin mash (I didn't have canned pumpkin but I did have a huge jack o' lantern!), which I cut with whole yogurt, maybe 1/2 cup. My god, this cakey bread is MOIST and delicious!

